This paper proposes a method to improve the generalization capacity of metric-based methods for few-shot learning. The paper focuses on developing a unified framework to learn a more discriminative metric space, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
